    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>[Glenridding House, Patterdale.]</placeName>
                    <date>June 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.—</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>My mind was so full of the Ceylon affair that I quite forgot to thank you about the microscope, which my son finds excellent.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> When next you see Prof. Abbe, I hope that you will give him my best thanks for his great kindness.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13213.xml">letter from Ernst Haeckel, 21 June 1881</ref> and n. 8; <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml">Francis Darwin</ref> had recently received a Zeiss microscope. For Haeckel’s planned research trip to Ceylon (Sri Lanka), see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13218.xml">letter to Ernst Haeckel, 25 June 1881</ref>. 
            </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5.xml">Ernst Abbe</ref> had personally supervised the fine optical work on Francis’s microscope (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-13213.xml">letter from Ernst Haeckel, 21 June 1881</ref>).</note>
        </div>   
       
